Step 1: Identify revenue
- Main Business Revenue: 7099920.95
- Total Revenue: 7099920.95

Step 2: Identify cost
- Cost of Goods Sold: 5540000.00
- Total Cost: 5540000.00

Step 3: Calculate difference between revenue and cost
Difference = Total Revenue - Total Cost = 7099920.95 - 5540000.00 = 1559920.95

Step 4: Identify line item that represents this difference
The "Gross Profit" matches this value: 1559920.95

Hence, the value to be extracted is 1559920.95.
